body:
File: compiler/js-typed-lowering.cc
Symbol: JSTypedLowering::ReduceJSEqual / ReduceJSStrictEqual
Excerpt: The code implements folding of JSEqual when one input is NullOrUndefined to ObjectIsUndetectable. Key lines:
- JSTypedLowering::ReduceJSEqual: if (r.OneInputIs(Type::NullOrUndefined())) { RelaxEffectsAndControls(node); node->RemoveInput(...); NodeProperties::ChangeOp(node, simplified()->ObjectIsUndetectable()); return Changed(node); }
- Also handles ReceiverOrNullOrUndefined case by emitting JSGraphAssembler code that uses ObjectIsUndetectable and ReferenceEqual.
- ReduceJSStrictEqual handles ReceiverOrNullOrUndefined, using ReferenceEqual; not folding to undetectable except via typed lowering earlier.
Dependencies: uses dependencies() via broker()->dependencies() and may need protector registration elsewhere (CompilationDependencies::DependOnNoUndetectableObjectsProtector is used in turboshaft machine lowering and JSTypedLowering sometimes uses dependencies()->DependOn... for other protectors.)
FileLine: compiler/js-typed-lowering.cc:892-980
explanation: This entry extracts the exact JSTypedLowering reducers that fold abstract equality with null/undefined to ObjectIsUndetectable and the strict-equal handling.
